snippet.textDisplay: CS Pakistan after Rohail Hayat left, Season 7 definitely felt like it needs Rohail Hayat back. However, season 8 and especially by season 9 the CS Pakistan has not only taken back the excellence but have increased the talent, excellence and variety of music from within the Pak/Indian musicians and singers. Definitely beats the Bollywood/Hollywood style singing/dancing. The real soul satisfying singing, ethnic music and talents of sufi and other singing has been revived so well by CSP. Please keep it up.
snippet.textOriginal: CS Pakistan after Rohail Hayat left, Season 7 definitely felt like it needs Rohail Hayat back. However, season 8 and especially by season 9 the CS Pakistan has not only taken back the excellence but have increased the talent, excellence and variety of music from within the Pak/Indian musicians and singers. Definitely beats the Bollywood/Hollywood style singing/dancing. The real soul satisfying singing, ethnic music and talents of sufi and other singing has been revived so well by CSP. Please keep it up.

snippet.textDisplay: Summy was a beautiful girl from Cholistan, living with her mother. She was kidnapped by a village ruffian. Her mother in the absence of her daughter used to cry and often does walling. Her lamenting change into words, so the Summy folk lore was formed. So it is not a love song rather a lamenting of a mother for her daughter. There is a narration about this story that in Cholistan when rains do not fall for a long time and the drought lasts months.   i fell sad for her
